// VortXEdge.xcconfig.example  --  COMMITTED TEMPLATE (no real secret here).
//
// Copy this to `VortXEdge.xcconfig` (same directory) and fill in the real value to enable
// client-side request signing against the hardened VortX edge workers:
//
//     cp app/Config/VortXEdge.xcconfig.example app/Config/VortXEdge.xcconfig
//
// `VortXEdge.xcconfig` is GITIGNORED and MUST NEVER be committed. The VortX repo is public; a
// secret in git history is leaked forever. Keep the real value only in the local gitignored file
// and in CI (a GitHub Actions repo secret), never in the tracked tree.
//
// VORTX_EDGE_SECRET is the 64-char hex shared secret. It is read at runtime from Info.plist
// (key `VortXEdgeSecret`, which substitutes $(VORTX_EDGE_SECRET) at build time) by
// SourcesShared/VortXEdgeAuth.swift, which signs requests to OUR gated edge hosts
// (skip / trickplay / ratings / poster / erdb / trailer .vortx.tv) with X-VX-Ts + X-VX-Sig.
//
// EMPTY is safe: the workers run in OBSERVE mode, so an absent/empty secret produces a no-op /
// empty-key signature that observe lets through. Leave it blank for local builds; the owner
// provisions the real value before enforce is flipped on.
VORTX_EDGE_SECRET =
